    "description": "<p>When you take damage, you can use your reaction to exploit chaos to protect yourself.</p>\n<p>Roll 3d6 and check the individual values of the dice on the following table:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 67.1876px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 21.1548%;\"><col style=\"width: 78.8452%;\"></colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16.7969px;\"><strong>3d6 Result</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16.7969px;\">Distinct Values</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">You reduce the amount of damage by the result of the highest dice, plus your spellcasting modifier (minimum 1).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16.7969px;\">2 of a Kind</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">You take half damage, and your assailant takes the other half of the damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 16.7969px;\">3 of a Kind</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">Your assailant takes that damage instead, and you take no damage.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Additionally, you gain temporary hit points equals to the highest die. Those temporary hit points last for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
